  "response_text": "A man sits at a breakfast tray in a dark, wood-panelled room decorated with Western objects. He wears a large pale cowboy hat, a light blue suit jacket with darker blue panels, a white shirt, and a blue tie. Behind him are a bright curtained window, a small rearing-horse statue, a model oil derrick, a horse painting, and stacked books. On the tray in front of him are a glass of orange juice, a bowl or plate of Frosted Mini-Wheats, a white dish, a pink napkin, and a red Kellogg’s Frosted Mini-Wheats cereal box standing upright beside him. He holds a spoon with a square cereal piece on it and speaks toward the viewer, then looks down at his food and gestures with his free hand, as if explaining the cereal’s two sides. The red box is clearly visible, with “Kellogg’s Frosted Mini-Wheats” printed on the front and a picture of the cereal in a bowl.\n\nAs he lowers his head, the brim of the cowboy hat hides much of his face. When he lifts his face again, a young boy is now sitting in the same place, wearing the oversized cowboy hat and the same light blue jacket and tie. The hat sits broadly around his small face. He smiles eagerly, holding up the spoonful of cereal, with the cereal box still upright to his right and the orange juice in front of him. He leans forward with an excited expression, looking straight ahead as if addressing the viewer.\n\nThe scene changes to a ballet dressing room. An adult ballerina sits at a dressing table in a white tutu with feathery trim and a small tiara or headpiece in her hair. The room has a theatrical backstage feel: a lit vanity mirror glows on the left, costumes hang in the background, and a shaft of light falls from above. On the tabletop are a bowl of cereal, a red Frosted Mini-Wheats box, a white pitcher of milk, a mug, and a plate with breakfast food. The ballerina holds a spoon in one hand and extends it outward while speaking. She sits upright and poised, her expression calm and composed, with the cereal box prominently beside her.\n\nThe ballerina continues holding the spoon near shoulder height, then the person at the table changes into a little girl dressed as a ballerina. The child has a white tutu, a small sparkling headpiece, and short dark hair partly covered by white feathers. She smiles brightly at the viewer, holding the spoon over a pink bowl filled with Mini-Wheats. The red cereal box remains beside her, almost as tall as her seated torso. She brings her other hand to her chest in a delighted gesture, then looks down toward the spoon and bowl with a pleased, giggling expression.\n\nA product display follows. The red Kellogg’s Frosted Mini-Wheats box stands centered on a red tabletop. Around it are breakfast items: a glass of milk, a glass of orange juice, a white milk pitcher shaped like a small jug, a bowl of Mini-Wheats in the foreground, and a plate of toast or pancakes with a pat of butter. The box front again shows the brand name “Kellogg’s Frosted Mini-Wheats” and a serving suggestion image of the cereal in a bowl. Small copyright text for Kellogg appears near the bottom.\n\nThe view moves to a close look at a white bowl with a yellow rim, filled with rectangular shredded wheat biscuits. At first the pieces look beige and fibrous, showing the woven shredded wheat texture. Then the visible pieces appear with a white frosted coating, speckled with darker shredded-wheat flecks. The cereal fills the bowl in chunky rectangular pillows. Beneath the bowl, pink on-screen text reads “Delicious & Nutritious.”\n\nThe final setting is a martial arts room with a glossy black table in front and pale grid-like shoji screens behind. Red panels with circular designs hang on the back wall, and a vertical wall scroll with Asian characters is visible to the side. A young boy with straight dark hair sits at the low table wearing a white martial arts uniform with dark patterned trim and round patches. In front of him are a bowl of cereal, a glass of milk, a glass of orange juice, and a small dark teapot-like vessel. The red Frosted Mini-Wheats box stands to his right. He holds a spoon with a cereal piece and looks forward, speaking with a serious, focused expression that turns into a small smile.\n\nThe boy raises one hand beside the cereal box and lifts a small pinkish cereal piece or Mini-Wheat in a demonstrative gesture. A close view then shows a single rectangular Mini-Wheat resting on a spoon: first the plain shredded wheat side is visible, beige and fibrous, then the piece is shown with its white frosted side facing outward. The frosted coating looks thick and sugary, with tiny dark flecks of wheat showing through.\n\nBack in the martial arts room, an adult man now sits in the same place, wearing the same style of white martial arts uniform with dark trim and a round chest patch. He has short dark hair and smiles broadly while holding a spoonful of cereal. The red Frosted Mini-Wheats box remains beside him. He gestures toward the viewer with the spoon, then makes a flat-handed chopping motion in front of the box, as if punctuating his words. At the end, he lifts a rectangular piece of toast or breakfast bread in his other hand, holding it up beside his face while still smiling, with the cereal bowl and product box in front of him.",
